## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Class Structure Block Diagram

This Mermaid diagram shows the internal anatomy of a Java class with all member categories visible.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["CLASS Student"] --> B["FIELDS - STATE"]
    A --> C["CONSTRUCTORS - INITIALIZATION"]
    A --> D["METHODS - BEHAVIOR"]
    A --> E["STATIC MEMBERS - CLASS LEVEL"]
    A --> F["NESTED TYPES - OPTIONAL"]

    B --> B1["private String name"]
    B --> B2["private int rollNumber"]
    B --> B3["private double cgpa"]

    C --> C1["public Student() - DEFAULT"]
    C --> C2["public Student String int double - PARAMETERIZED"]
    C --> C3["public Student Student - COPY"]

    D --> D1["public void displayDetails"]
    D --> D2["public void updateCGPA double"]
    D --> D3["public String getName"]

    E --> E1["private static int studentCount"]
    E --> E2["public static int getStudentCount"]

    F --> F1["inner class if any"]
```

### 4.2 Object Creation Flowchart

This sequence diagram traces the runtime flow when `new Student("Ananya", 45, 9.2)` is executed.

```mermaid
graph TD
    START["main method starts"] --> REF["Reference s2 declared on STACK"]
    REF --> NEW["new Student invoked"]
    NEW --> ALLOC["JVM allocates memory in HEAP"]
    ALLOC --> DEFAULT_INIT["Default initialization of fields name=null rollNumber=0 cgpa=0.0"]
    DEFAULT_INIT --> CTOR["Parameterized constructor invoked"]
    CTOR --> THIS_BIND["this reference binds to new object"]
    THIS_BIND --> ASSIGN["Field assignments executed"]
    ASSIGN --> RET["Constructor returns heap address"]
    RET --> LINK["Reference s2 linked to heap address"]
    LINK --> USABLE["Object s2 is now usable"]
    USABLE --> END["main method continues"]
```

### 4.3 JVM Memory Architecture тАФ Block-Level View

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph STACK["STACK MEMORY - per Thread"]
        S1["main frame"]
        S2["s1 reference"]
        S3["s2 reference"]
        S4["s3 reference"]
    end

    subgraph HEAP["HEAP MEMORY - Shared"]
        H1["Student object 1 - name Not Assigned - roll 0 - cgpa 0.0"]
        H2["Student object 2 - name Ananya - roll 45 - cgpa 9.2"]
        H3["Student object 3 - name Ananya - roll 45 - cgpa 9.2"]
    end

    subgraph METH["METHOD AREA - Class Metadata"]
        M1["Student.class bytecode"]
        M2["Static variable studentCount"]
        M3["Method displayDetails code"]
        M4["Method updateCGPA code"]
    end

    S2 -.points to.-> H1
    S3 -.points to.-> H2
    S4 -.points to.-> H3
```

### 4.4 Access Modifier Decision Tree

```mermaid
graph TD
    Q1{"Need visibility outside class?"}
    Q1 -- "No" --> A1["Use PRIVATE"]
    Q1 -- "Yes" --> Q2{"Within same package only?"}
    Q2 -- "Yes" --> A2["Use DEFAULT - no modifier"]
    Q2 -- "No" --> Q3{"Subclasses in other packages?"}
    Q3 -- "Yes" --> A3["Use PROTECTED"]
    Q3 -- "No" --> A4["Use PUBLIC"]
```

---

<!-- SECTION_4_END -->

