    }
}

class TestDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo.show();
    }
}
```

### Output

```
Static Block 1 executed
Static Block 2 executed. b = 40
a = 10, b = 40
```

### Analysis

- The `main()` method triggers class loading.
- Static variables are initialized first (`a = 10`, `b = 0`).
- Static blocks execute **in the order they appear** in the source file.
- Finally, `show()` is invoked тАФ by this point all static initializations are complete.
