## Part B Questions (14 Marks тАФ KTU ESE Style with Internal Choice)

### Question A (14 Marks)

**(a) Explain static variables, static methods, and static blocks in Java with suitable examples. Mention any four restrictions on static methods. (7 Marks)**

#### Model Solution

**Static Variable:**
A static variable is a class-level variable declared with the `static` keyword. Only one copy exists per class, shared by all objects. It is initialized when the class is loaded.

```java
class College {
    static String collegeName = "KTU";
    int rollNo;
    College(int r) { rollNo = r; }
}
```

**Static Method:**
A static method belongs to the class, not to objects. It is invoked via `ClassName.methodName()` and can directly access only static members.

```java
class MathUtil {
    static int square(int x) { return x * x; }
}
// Call: MathUtil.square(5);
```

**Static Block:**
A static block is a code block prefixed with `static` that executes **once** when the class is first loaded, used for initialization.

```java
class DBConfig {
    static String url;
    static {
        url = "jdbc:mysql://localhost/ktu";
        System.out.println("DB initialized");
    }
}
```

**Four Restrictions on Static Methods:**

1. Cannot use the `this` keyword.
2. Cannot use the `super` keyword.
3. Cannot directly access non-static (instance) variables.
4. Cannot directly call non-static (instance) methods тАФ must be invoked through an object reference.

