## 2.4 Real-World Engineering Utility

| Concept | Real-World Use Case |
|---------|---------------------|
| Member Inner Class | Implementing data structures (`LinkedList.Node`, `TreeMap.Entry`) |
| Static Nested Class | Builder pattern, factory methods, grouping constants |
| Local Inner Class | Algorithm-specific helpers within a method (e.g., quick-sort comparators) |
| Anonymous Inner Class | Event handlers (`ActionListener`), `Runnable`/`Thread` tasks, callback mechanisms |
| Inheritance (Super Class) | GUI frameworks (`JFrame` тЖТ `MyFrame`), exception hierarchy, JDBC drivers |
| `super` keyword | Template Method design pattern, framework extension points |

---

## 2.5 KTU Frequently Confused Points

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Pitfall 1:** `this` refers to the **current object**. `super` refers to the **parent class portion** of the current object. They are different.
> **Common Pitfall 2:** Static methods are **not** overridden; they are **hidden**. Calling `super.staticMethod()` is **illegal** in Java.
> **Common Pitfall 3:** Constructors are **not inherited** and **not overridden**. They are only chained via `super()`.
> **Common Pitfall 4:** A local inner class can only access **effectively final** local variables of its enclosing method. Modifying `x` after declaration makes it non-final тЖТ compile error.
