## 3.2 Walkthrough 2: Static Nested Class (Full Code + Output)

### Code
```java
class University {
    static String name = "KTU Kerala";
    String location = "Thiruvananthapuram";

    // static nested class
    static class Department {
        void display() {
            // can access static member of outer
            System.out.println("University: " + name);
            // cannot directly access non-static 'location'
            // System.out.println(location);   // COMPILE ERROR
        }
    }
}

class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // No outer object needed!
        University.Department dept = new University.Department();
        dept.display();
    }
}
```

### Step-by-Step Explanation

| Step | Code | Explanation |
|------|------|-------------|
| 1 | `static class Department` | Marks the nested class as **static**. |
| 2 | `University.Department dept = new University.Department();` | Instantiation uses the standard `new` syntax тАФ **no outer instance required**. |
| 3 | `display()` accesses `name` | Works because `name` is a `static` member of the outer class. |
| 4 | Commented line | Would fail to compile because `location` is an instance field. |

### Expected Output
```
University: KTU Kerala
```

