## 3.6 Analytical Matrix: When to Use What?

| Scenario | Best Choice | Reason |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| Helper class needs full access to outer instance | **Member Inner Class** | Direct access to non-static outer members |
| Helper class logically belongs to outer but is self-contained | **Static Nested Class** | No need for outer instance; namespace clarity |
| Helper class used only inside one method | **Local Inner Class** | Scope-limited; no leakage outside the method |
| One-off implementation of interface/abstract class | **Anonymous Inner Class** | Concise, inline, used heavily in event handling |
| Reuse fields/methods across related classes | **Inheritance (Super Class)** | Code reuse, IS-A relationship, polymorphism |
| Need to call parent constructor explicitly | **`super(args)`** | Custom initialisation chain |
| Need to refer to parent method hidden by override | **`super.methodName()`** | Preserves parent behaviour in overridden version |
