## PART A тАФ Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question 1 [KTU University Exam тАФ June 2024, Model QP]
**Differentiate between a member inner class and a static nested class in Java with suitable examples.**

#### Model Answer (3 Marks)

| Feature | Member Inner Class | Static Nested Class |
|---------|-------------------|---------------------|
| **Keyword** | No `static` keyword used | Declared with `static` |
| **Outer instance needed?** | Yes тАФ to instantiate | No |
| **Access to outer members** | Can access all (including private) | Only static members |
| **Declaration of static members** | Not allowed (classic rule) | Allowed |
| **Instantiation syntax** | `outerObj.new Inner()` | `new Outer.Nested()` |

**Example тАФ Member Inner Class:**
```java
class Outer {
    class Inner {
        void show() { System.out.println("Member inner"); }
    }
}
// To use:
Outer o = new Outer();
Outer.Inner i = o.new Inner();
```

**Example тАФ Static Nested Class:**
```java
class Outer {
    static class Nested {
        void show() { System.out.println("Static nested"); }
    }
}
// To use:
Outer.Nested n = new Outer.Nested();
```

> [!TIP]
> **For full 3 marks:** Mention the **instantiation syntax difference** тАФ it is the most distinguishing point and the one students forget.

