**Q A. [KTU University Exam тАФ May 2024, Module 2, 14 Marks]**

**(a) Explain the concept of subclass and superclass in Java with a suitable example. Discuss the `extends` keyword, the IS-A relationship, and what members are inherited. (7 marks)**

**Model Solution:**

A **superclass** is a general class that defines common attributes and behaviors, while a **subclass** is a specialized class that inherits these features and can add or override them. The `extends` keyword establishes a single-line inheritance link in Java.

```java
class Shape {                       // superclass
    String color = "red";
    void draw() { System.out.println("Drawing shape"); }
}

class Circle extends Shape {        // subclass
    double radius = 5.0;
    @Override
    void draw() { System.out.println("Drawing circle of color " + color); }
}
```

**Inherited members in `Circle`:**

- `color` (public field) тАФ directly accessible.
- `draw()` тАФ inherited and then overridden.
- All public/protected methods of `Shape` (none defined here beyond `draw`).

**Not inherited:**

- Private fields of `Shape` (if any).
- Constructors of `Shape`.

**IS-A relationship:** `Circle IS-A Shape`. Hence, an `Shape` reference can hold a `Circle` object: `Shape s = new Circle();`

> **Mark split:** Definition тАФ 2, `extends` example тАФ 2, IS-A explanation тАФ 1, Inherited vs not-inherited тАФ 2.

