### 5.3 тЪая╕П KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Where students most-commonly lose marks on Subclass questions:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting that constructors are NOT inherited.** Students often write *"subclass inherits the constructor of the superclass"*. This is **wrong**. Constructors are *called* via `super()`, not inherited.
> 2. **Confusing `super` and `this`.** Both must appear on the first line of a constructor тАФ they **cannot** coexist.
> 3. **Claiming `private` members are inherited.** They are physically present in the parent's memory, but not *directly accessible* in the subclass without a getter/setter.
> 4. **Omitting `@Override` annotation** when overriding тАФ leads to silent bugs (overloading instead of overriding) that cost method-dispatch marks.
> 5. **Forgetting to import or use correct access** тАФ `protected` is the most-tested modifier in KTU papers because it straddles inheritance and access control.
> 6. **Mis-stating "IS-A":** Saying *"Car HAS-A Vehicle"* instead of *"Car IS-A Vehicle"*. Composition ("has-a") is **not** inheritance.

