# SECTION 3: Step-by-Step Code Analysis & Execution Traces

## 3.1 Example 1 тАФ Single-Class Constructor Chaining with `this()`

```java
class Box {
    int length, breadth, height;

    // Constructor 1: no-arg
    Box() {
        this(10, 10, 10);   // delegates to Constructor 3
        System.out.println("Box() - default cube");
    }

    // Constructor 2: one arg
    Box(int size) {
        this(size, size, size);  // delegates to Constructor 3
        System.out.println("Box(int) - cube of size " + size);
    }

    // Constructor 3: three args
    Box(int l, int b, int h) {
        this.length = l;
        this.breadth = b;
        this.height = h;
        System.out.println("Box(int,int,int) - l=" + l + " b=" + b + " h=" + h);
    }
}
```

### Execution Trace for `new Box();`

| Step | Action | Output So Far |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `new Box()` invokes **Constructor 1** | тАФ |
| 2 | Constructor 1 calls `this(10,10,10)` | тАФ |
| 3 | **Constructor 3** begins executing | тАФ |
| 4 | `length=10, breadth=10, height=10` assigned | `Box(int,int,int) - l=10 b=10 h=10` |
| 5 | Control returns to **Constructor 1** | `Box() - default cube` |

**Final Console Output (order of appearance):**
```
Box(int,int,int) - l=10 b=10 h=10
Box() - default cube
```

## 3.2 Example 2 тАФ Multi-Level Inheritance Constructor Order

```java
class Vehicle {                      // Level 1
    Vehicle() {
        System.out.println("Vehicle constructor");
