## 3.3 Example 3 тАФ Complete Trace: Static + Instance + Inheritance

```java
class Alpha {
    static {
        System.out.println("1. Static block of Alpha");
    }
    {
        System.out.println("3. Instance block of Alpha");
    }
    Alpha() {
        System.out.println("4. Alpha constructor");
    }
}

class Beta extends Alpha {
    static {
        System.out.println("2. Static block of Beta");
    }
    {
        System.out.println("5. Instance block of Beta");
    }
    Beta() {
        System.out.println("6. Beta constructor");
    }
}
```

### Step-by-Step Logical Deduction for `new Beta();`

**Stage A тАФ Class Loading (happens once):**

$$
\text{Order} = \text{Alpha's static block} \rightarrow \text{Beta's static block}
$$

**Stage B тАФ Object Construction (happens for each `new`):**

$$
\text{Order} = \text{super() call} \rightarrow \text{Alpha's instance block} \rightarrow \text{Alpha constructor} \rightarrow \text{Beta's instance block} \rightarrow \text{Beta constructor}
$$

**Final Console Output (numbered to match trace):**
```
1. Static block of Alpha
2. Static block of Beta
3. Instance block of Alpha
4. Alpha constructor
5. Instance block of Beta
6. Beta constructor
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Logical Justification:** Static blocks belong to the **class** and execute when the class is **loaded**, not when an object is created. Since `Beta` extends `Alpha`, the JVM loads `Alpha.class` first, triggering Alpha's static block, then loads `Beta.class`, triggering Beta's static block. Only **after** both classes are loaded does object construction begin.

## 3.4 Example 4 тАФ Constructor Overloading with Parameterized Super Call

```java
class Employee {
    String name;
    int id;
    Employee(String n, int i) {
        this.name = n;
        this.id = i;
        System.out.println("Employee: " + name + " (" + id + ")");
    }
}

class Manager extends Employee {
    String department;
    Manager(String n, int i, String dept) {
        super(n, i);   // MUST be explicit тАФ Employee has no default constructor
