    }
}
```

### Deduction of Compilation Rule

$$
\text{If } \exists \text{ constructor in Parent} \land \text{no no-arg constructor defined} \Rightarrow \text{Child MUST call super(args)}
$$

| Line | Step | Result |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Compile `Employee` | тЬЕ No errors тАФ has `Employee(String, int)` |
| 2 | Compile `Manager` without `super(n,i)` | тЭМ **Error:** no suitable constructor found for `Employee()` |
| 3 | Add `super(n, i)` as first line | тЬЕ Compiles |
| 4 | Run `new Manager("Asha", 101, "IT")` | Output: `Employee: Asha (101)` then `Manager of: IT` |

