### **Question 2** `[KTU University Exam тАУ Dec 2023]`
**Explain the role of `super()` in determining the order of constructor execution in inheritance.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
When an object of a subclass is created, the JVM implicitly inserts a call to `super()` as the first statement of the subclass constructor. This invokes the parent class constructor, ensuring that **inherited members are initialized before the subclass body executes**. The call chain travels upward through the hierarchy (Child тЖТ Parent тЖТ ... тЖТ Object) and then body execution proceeds downward. If the parent class does not define a no-argument constructor, the subclass must explicitly call `super(arguments)`. *(1 mark for implicit insertion rule, 1 mark for top-down execution, 1 mark for explicit super requirement.)*

