**(b) Differentiate between `this()` and `super()` in the context of constructor calls. Provide a unified Java program that demonstrates both in a single class hierarchy.** **(7 marks)**

**Model Solution:**

| Feature | `this()` | `super()` |
|---|---|---|
| Purpose | Calls another constructor of the **same** class | Calls a constructor of the **parent** class |
| Position | Must be the **first** statement | Must be the **first** statement |
| Coexistence | Cannot coexist with `super()` in the same constructor | Cannot coexist with `this()` in the same constructor |
