## 3.2 Worked Example 2: Abstract Class with Constructor (Advanced)

This example demonstrates the often-missed concept that **abstract classes CAN have constructors**, which are used by subclasses for initialization.

```java
// Abstract class with a parameterized constructor
abstract class Employee {
    String name;
    int id;

    // Constructor in abstract class тАФ perfectly legal
    Employee(String name, int id) {
        this.name = name;
        this.id = id;
        System.out.println("Employee constructor invoked for " + name);
    }

    abstract double calculateSalary();

    void displayInfo() {
        System.out.println("ID: " + id + ", Name: " + name);
    }
}

class FullTimeEmployee extends Employee {
    double monthlySalary;

    FullTimeEmployee(String name, int id, double monthlySalary) {
        super(name, id);                       // invoking abstract class constructor
        this.monthlySalary = monthlySalary;
    }

    @Override
    double calculateSalary() {
        return monthlySalary;
    }
}

class PartTimeEmployee extends Employee {
    double hourlyRate;
    int hoursWorked;

    PartTimeEmployee(String name, int id, double hourlyRate, int hoursWorked) {
        super(name, id);
        this.hourlyRate = hourlyRate;
        this.hoursWorked = hoursWorked;
    }

    @Override
    double calculateSalary() {
        return hourlyRate * hoursWorked;
    }
}

public class EmployeeDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Employee e1 = new FullTimeEmployee("Anand", 101, 50000);
        Employee e2 = new PartTimeEmployee("Beena", 102, 500, 40);

        e1.displayInfo();
        System.out.println("Salary: " + e1.calculateSalary());
        e2.displayInfo();
        System.out.println("Salary: " + e2.calculateSalary());
    }
}
```

### 3.2.1 Logical Flow of Constructor Chaining

| Step | Action |
|---|---|
| 1 | `new FullTimeEmployee("Anand", 101, 50000)` is called. |
| 2 | `FullTimeEmployee` constructor begins. |
| 3 | `super(name, id)` invokes `Employee(String, int)`. |
| 4 | `Employee` constructor initializes `name` and `id`, prints message. |
| 5 | Control returns to `FullTimeEmployee` constructor, sets `monthlySalary`. |
| 6 | Object is fully constructed. |

**Output:**
```
Employee constructor invoked for Anand
Employee constructor invoked for Beena
ID: 101, Name: Anand
Salary: 50000.0
ID: 102, Name: Beena
Salary: 20000.0
```

