## ЁЯУШ PART A тАФ Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question 1
**[KTU University Exam тАФ May 2024, Model Question Paper]**

**Define an abstract class in Java. Can we create an object of an abstract class? Justify your answer.**

**Model Answer (Expected Length: 6тАУ8 lines):**

An abstract class in Java is a class declared with the `abstract` keyword that may contain abstract methods (methods without implementation) and concrete methods (methods with implementation). It represents a generalized blueprint and is used to enforce a contract upon its subclasses.

**No, we cannot create an object of an abstract class directly.** If we attempt `new AbstractClassName()`, the compiler raises an error: *"ClassName is abstract; cannot be instantiated"*. The reason is that an abstract class may have unimplemented abstract methods, and allowing direct instantiation would produce objects whose methods have no body, leading to undefined behavior. Objects can only be created through concrete subclasses that have implemented all abstract methods.

