### Question 2
**[KTU University Exam тАФ Dec 2023, Retest Paper]**

**List any four rules that must be followed when using abstract methods in Java.**

**Model Answer:**

1. **Mandatory Override:** Any concrete (non-abstract) subclass must implement all inherited abstract methods; otherwise, the subclass itself must be declared abstract.
2. **No Body Allowed:** An abstract method is declared with a semicolon and has no method body.
3. **Illegal Modifiers:** Abstract methods cannot be declared as `static`, `final`, `private`, or `synchronized`, because these modifiers conflict with the requirement that the method must be overridden.
4. **Class Must Be Abstract:** If a class contains even one abstract method, the class itself must be declared `abstract`.
5. **Visibility:** Abstract methods cannot have a lower visibility in the subclass (i.e., a `public` abstract method cannot be overridden as `protected`).

