#### Model Solution for Question B(a)

**Tabular Comparison:**

| Property | Abstract Class | Concrete Class |
|---|---|---|
| Keyword | `abstract` | None |
| Abstract Methods | Allowed | Not allowed |
| Instantiation | Cannot be instantiated | Can be instantiated |
| Purpose | Partial implementation / contract | Full implementation |
| Example | `abstract class Shape { abstract double area(); }` | `class Circle { double area() { return 3.14 * r * r; } }` |

**Code Example:**

```java
// Abstract class example
abstract class Animal {
    abstract void sound();         // contract тАФ no body
    void sleep() {                  // shared behavior
        System.out.println("Sleeping...");
    }
}

// Concrete class example
class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Bark");
    }
}

public class TestAbstract {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Animal a = new Animal();  // COMPILE ERROR
        Animal d = new Dog();
        d.sound();   // Bark
        d.sleep();   // Sleeping...
    }
}
