### Q1. [KTU University Exam тАУ Dec 2023, Model Question Paper]

**Define an interface in Java. List any four differences between an interface and an abstract class.**

**Model Answer (3 marks тАФ board-validated structure):**

An **interface** in Java is a blueprint of a class that contains only **abstract methods** (pre-Java 8) and **constants**. It specifies *what* a class must do, but not *how*. It is used to achieve **full abstraction** and **multiple inheritance** in Java.

**Differences between Interface and Abstract Class:**

| Sl. No. | Interface | Abstract Class |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | All methods are implicitly `public abstract` (Java 7) | Can have abstract and non-abstract (concrete) methods |
| 2 | Fields are implicitly `public static final` | Fields can be any access modifier, non-final |
| 3 | A class can implement **multiple** interfaces | A class can extend only **one** abstract class |
| 4 | Declared using the `interface` keyword | Declared using the `abstract class` keywords |
| 5 | Cannot have constructors | Can have constructors |
| 6 | Cannot have instance methods (Java 7) | Can have instance methods with body |

*(Any four differences тАФ ┬╜ mark each + 1 mark for the definition = 3 marks)*

---

### Q2. [KTU University Exam тАУ June 2024, Expected Pattern]

**What is a functional interface in Java? Give one example with a lambda expression.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

A **functional interface** is an interface that contains **exactly one abstract method**. It is also known as a **Single Abstract Method (SAM)** interface. It can optionally be annotated with `@FunctionalInterface` to enable compile-time validation.

Functional interfaces are the foundation of **lambda expressions** in Java 8, enabling functional programming.

**Example:**

```java
@FunctionalInterface
interface SquareCalculator {
    int square(int x);
}

public class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SquareCalculator sc = (x) -> x * x;   // lambda
        System.out.println(sc.square(7));      // Output: 49
    }
}
```

*(1 mark definition + 1 mark example interface + 1 mark lambda code = 3 marks)*

