## ЁЯОп Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Last-Minute Revision Checklist)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Print this section or screenshot it тАФ this is your **exam-day cheat sheet**.

- тЬЕ **Interface = Pure Contract** тАФ defines *what*, not *how*.
- тЬЕ **Cannot be instantiated** тАФ `new InterfaceName()` is a compile error.
- тЬЕ **All fields are implicitly `public static final`** тАФ constants only.
- тЬЕ **Pre-Java 8:** all methods are implicitly `public abstract` (no body).
- тЬЕ **Java 8+:** interfaces can have `default` and `static` methods with body.
- тЬЕ **Java 9+:** interfaces can have `private` methods (rarely asked in KTU).
- тЬЕ **A class uses `implements` keyword** тАФ `class C implements I`.
- тЬЕ **Multiple interface implementation is allowed** тАФ `class C implements I1, I2, I3`.
- тЬЕ **Interfaces use `extends` (not `implements`) to inherit** тАФ `interface I2 extends I1`.
- тЬЕ **Interface can extend multiple interfaces** тАФ `interface I3 extends I1, I2`.
- тЬЕ **Interface cannot extend a class** тАФ only extends other interfaces.
- тЬЕ **Diamond Problem Resolution Hierarchy:** class method > sub-interface default > compile error (must override).
- тЬЕ **Static methods in interfaces are NOT inherited** тАФ call as `InterfaceName.method()`.
- тЬЕ **Functional Interface = exactly ONE abstract method** тАФ use `@FunctionalInterface` annotation.
- тЬЕ **Lambda expressions work ONLY with functional interfaces.**
- тЬЕ **Polymorphic reference:** `InterfaceName ref = new ConcreteClass();` тЖТ dynamic dispatch at runtime.
- тЬЕ **Open/Closed Principle:** Add new implementations without modifying client code that uses the interface.
- тЬЕ **Loose Coupling:** Client depends on interface, not on concrete class тЖТ easier testing and maintenance.
- тЬЕ **Difference from Abstract Class:** Interfaces support multiple inheritance; abstract classes do not. Interfaces have no state; abstract classes can have instance variables.
- тЬЕ **Real-world examples to mention in exam:** `List`, `Map`, `Runnable`, `ActionListener`, `Comparable`, `Serializable`, `Connection` (JDBC).

> **ЁЯОУ KTU 2024 Board Exam Success Tip:** For every interface question, always structure your answer in three layers: **(1) Declaration of interface**, **(2) Implementation by concrete class(es)**, **(3) Client code demonstrating polymorphism**. This guarantees full marks regardless of the specific scenario given.

