| **Throw an exception** | `throw new ExceptionType("msg");` | `throw new IOException("File missing");` | **HIGH** |
| **Declare exception** | `methodName() throws ExceptionType` | `void read() throws IOException` | **HIGH** |
| **Catch exception** | `try { ... } catch(ExceptionType e) { ... }` | `catch(IOException e) { e.printStackTrace(); }` | **HIGH** |
| **Multi-catch (Java 7+)** | `catch (E1 \| E2 \| E3 e)` | `catch(IOException \| SQLException e)` | **MEDIUM** |
| **Finally block** | Always executes (except `System.exit()`) | Used for resource cleanup | **HIGH** |
| **Try-with-resources (Java 7+)** | `try (Resource r = new Resource()) { ... }` | Auto-closes `AutoCloseable` resources | **HIGH** |
| **Custom Checked Exception** | `class MyEx extends Exception { }` | User-defined checked exception | **HIGH** |
| **Override Rule** | Subclass тЙд Parent in checked exceptions | Cannot add new checked throws | **HIGH** |
| **Re-throw** | `throw e;` inside catch block | Preserves stack trace (better than `throw new`) | **MEDIUM** |
| **Chained Exceptions** | `new Exception("msg", cause);` | Wraps original exception as cause | **MEDIUM** |

