## 3.1 Derivation 1: Throwing a Pre-defined (Built-in) Unchecked Exception

### Complete Java Program

```java
// File: ThrowDemo1.java
public class ThrowDemo1 {

    // Static method that validates a candidate's age for voting
    static void validateAge(int age) {
        if (age < 18) {
            // Step 1: JVM creates a new ArithmeticException object
            // Step 2: Control immediately leaves this method
            throw new ArithmeticException(
                "Sorry, age must be 18 or above to register."
            );
        }
        // Step 3: This line is REACHED only if age >= 18
        System.out.println("Registration successful for age: " + age);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            System.out.println("--- Attempt 1: age = 13 ---");
            validateAge(13);   // Will trigger throw
            System.out.println("This line never executes.");
        } catch (ArithmeticException ex) {
            // Step 4: Nearest matching catch block receives the object
            System.out.println("Exception caught: " + ex.getMessage());
        }

        System.out.println("\n--- Attempt 2: age = 25 ---");
        validateAge(25);      // Normal path тАФ no exception
        System.out.println("Program finished normally.");
    }
}
```

### Expected Output

```
--- Attempt 1: age = 13 ---
Exception caught: Sorry, age must be 18 or above to register.

--- Attempt 2: age = 25 ---
Registration successful for age: 25
Program finished normally.
```

### Execution Trace (the "How" Behind Every Line)

| **Step** | **What happens internally** | **Visible effect** |
|:-:|---|---|
| 1 | `main` begins, prints header | "--- Attempt 1: age = 13 ---" |
| 2 | `validateAge(13)` called; `if (13 < 18)` is **true** | тАФ |
| 3 | `new ArithmeticException("SorryтАж")` invokes the constructor; stack-trace is captured | Object reference passed to `throw` |
| 4 | `throw` **aborts** `validateAge`; control returns to `main` | тАФ |
| 5 | JVM inspects the enclosing `try` block in `main`; finds a `catch (ArithmeticException тАж)` тАФ **type matches** | тАФ |
| 6 | `catch` body executes; `ex.getMessage()` returns the string passed to the constructor | "Exception caught: Sorry, age must be 18тАж" |
| 7 | `main` resumes after `catch`; second `validateAge(25)` call | "--- Attempt 2: age = 25 ---" |
| 8 | `if (25 < 18)` is **false**; "Registration successfulтАж" prints | "Registration successful for age: 25" |
| 9 | `main` ends normally; JVM exits with code 0 | "Program finished normally." |

