#### Model Solution for (a)

**Explanation of `throw`:** The `throw` keyword is used to **explicitly throw** a single exception object. Syntax: `throw <ThrowableRef>;`. It transfers control immediately to the nearest matching `catch` block in the call stack.

**Complete Java Program:**

```java
// File: InvalidAgeException.java
// Step 1: Define the custom CHECKED exception
class InvalidAgeException extends Exception {
    public InvalidAgeException(String message) {
        super(message);
    }
}

// File: ThrowAgeDemo.java
public class ThrowAgeDemo {

    // Step 2: Method that throws the custom exception
    static void register(String name, int age) throws InvalidAgeException {
        if (age < 18) {
            // Step 3: Throw single exception object
            throw new InvalidAgeException(
                name + " is underage (" + age + "). Registration denied."
            );
        }
        System.out.println(name + " registered successfully.");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String[][] users = {
            {"Alice", "25"},
            {"Bob",    "15"},
            {"Carol",  "30"},
            {"Dave",   "12"}
