> **(a)** Discuss the rules and restrictions governing the use of the `throw` statement in Java. What happens if a `null` reference is thrown? Provide an example illustrating **re-throwing of an exception**. **(7 marks)**

> **(b)** Write a Java program to validate a password according to the following rules. Define a custom exception `WeakPasswordException`. The password must be **at least 8 characters long** and **contain at least one digit**. If the password fails any rule, throw the custom exception with a descriptive message. Use `try-catch` to demonstrate both valid and invalid cases. **(7 marks)**

