## 3.3 Derivation: String Constructors тАФ Code Walkthrough

```java
public class StringConstructorsDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        // 1. Default constructor тАФ empty string
        String s1 = new String();
        System.out.println("s1 = '" + s1 + "' (length: " + s1.length() + ")");

        // 2. Copy constructor
        String original = "Hello, KTU!";
        String s2 = new String(original);
        System.out.println("s2 = " + s2);

        // 3. char[] constructor тАФ full array
        char[] chars = {'K', 'T', 'U', ' ', '2', '0', '2', '4'};
        String s3 = new String(chars);
        System.out.println("s3 = " + s3);

        // 4. char[] subarray constructor тАФ offset + count
        String s4 = new String(chars, 0, 3);  // chars[0..2] = "KTU"
        System.out.println("s4 = " + s4);

        // 5. byte[] constructor with named charset
        byte[] utf8Bytes = "Caf├й".getBytes("UTF-8");
        String s5 = new String(utf8Bytes, "UTF-8");
        System.out.println("s5 = " + s5);

        // 6. byte[] subarray with Charset object
        String s6 = new String(utf8Bytes, 0, utf8Bytes.length, java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
        System.out.println("s6 = " + s6);

        // 7. StringBuffer constructor
        StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer("Mutable-to-Immutable");
        String s7 = new String(sb);
        System.out.println("s7 = " + s7);

        // 8. StringBuilder constructor
        StringBuilder sb2 = new StringBuilder("Modern Builder");
        String s8 = new String(sb2);
        System.out.println("s8 = " + s8);
    }
}
```

**Step-by-step derivation of output:**

1. `s1` is an **empty** String тАФ `length()` returns `0`. Output: `s1 = '' (length: 0)`.
2. `s2` is a **deep copy** of `original` тАФ modifying `s2` would not affect `original` (though Strings are immutable anyway, this is a defensive copy mechanism).
3. `s3` converts the entire `char[]` to `"KTU 2024"`.
4. `s4` extracts a **substring** of the char array starting at index `0` with count `3` тАФ yielding `"KTU"`.
5. `s5` decodes UTF-8 bytes back to `"Caf├й"` тАФ proves proper character encoding.
6. `s6` does the same using a `Charset` object (type-safe, Java 1.6+).
7. `s7` snapshots a `StringBuffer` (synchronized) into an immutable `String`.
8. `s8` snapshots a `StringBuilder` (non-synchronized) into an immutable `String`.

**Final Output:**
```
s1 = '' (length: 0)
s2 = Hello, KTU!
s3 = KTU 2024
s4 = KTU
s5 = Caf├й
s6 = Caf├й
s7 = Mutable-to-Immutable
s8 = Modern Builder
```

> [!NOTE]
> **KTU Tip:** The `String(StringBuilder)` constructor was introduced in **Java 1.5** alongside the `StringBuilder` class. Before that, only `String(StringBuffer)` existed. KTU may test this historical fact.

