> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning тАФ Common Pitfalls:**
> 1. **Confusing `throw` with `throws`:** Students often mix these up. Remember: `throw` is a **statement** (inside the body); `throws` is a **declaration** (in the signature).
> 2. **Forgetting that `finally` runs even on `return`:** Many students incorrectly believe `finally` is skipped when a `return` is encountered. It is **not** skipped.
> 3. **Default charset trap:** Using `new String(byte[])` without specifying a charset can cause platform-dependent bugs. Always prefer `new String(byte[], Charset)` or `new String(byte[], "UTF-8")`.
> 4. **`String(StringBuilder)` vs `String(StringBuffer)`:** Both convert to immutable String, but `StringBuffer` is synchronized; `StringBuilder` is not. KTU may ask for this distinction.
> 5. **Overriding rule with `throws`:** When overriding, you **cannot** add new checked exceptions тАФ only same, fewer, or narrower ones. This is a frequent 2-mark question.
> 6. **`System.exit()` bypasses `finally`:** Students often say `finally` *always* runs тАФ this is **not true** when `System.exit()` is called.

