`Thread.suspend()` is a deprecated instance method of the `Thread` class that was used to **pause** the execution of a target thread. It is deprecated since **JDK 1.2** because the suspended thread **retains ownership of all the locks it holds**, which can lead to **deadlocks** if other threads try to acquire those same locks. The modern, safe alternative is `Object.wait()`, which releases the lock during the wait.

