## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common places students lose marks in this topic:**
> 1. **Confusing `Panel` default layout with `Frame` default layout.** (`Panel` тЖТ `FlowLayout`; `Frame` тЖТ `BorderLayout`.) тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 2. **Forgetting to call `setVisible(true)`** тАФ the program compiles and runs but nothing appears, confusing the student during the exam. тАФ **тИТ1 to 2 marks**
> 3. **Forgetting `addWindowListener`** тАФ clicking the X does not exit; examiner interprets this as incomplete code. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 4. **Using `setSize` on a container while a LayoutManager is active** тАФ the size may be overridden. With `null` layout, you *must* call `setBounds` on every child. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 5. **Writing "Container extends Object"** instead of "Container extends Component" тАФ destroys the IS-A relationship. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 6. **Confusing `TextField` (AWT) with `JTextField` (Swing)** тАФ `JTextField` is *not* part of AWT. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**

