## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember тЬЕ

- **`Component`** = any visible UI element; abstract class; root of all visual AWT classes.
- **`Container`** = a `Component` that can *hold* other components; abstract class.
- A **Container IS-A Component** (Composite Design Pattern).
- **Top-level containers** (`Frame`, `Dialog`) cannot be added to other containers; they interface directly with the OS.
- **Intermediate containers** (`Panel`, `ScrollPane`) must be placed inside a top-level container.
- Every container has a **Layout Manager** governing child placement.
- **`Frame` default = `BorderLayout`**, **`Panel` default = `FlowLayout`**.
- **`setLayout(null)`** disables auto-layout тАФ you must use `setBounds(x, y, w, h)` on every child.
- **Dynamic addition** of components requires `container.validate()` afterward.
- **`setVisible(true)`** must be called to actually display a container.
- **Window-close** handling requires registering a `WindowListener` (typically via `WindowAdapter`).
- `TextField` fires `ActionEvent` on **Enter** key тАФ basis of form-based input.
- The AWT hierarchy: `Object тЖТ Component тЖТ Container тЖТ {Panel, Window, ScrollPane}`; `Window тЖТ {Frame, Dialog}`; `Panel тЖТ Applet`.
