## 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. **[KTU University Exam тАУ Dec 2023]**
**Explain the Delegation Event Model used in Java Swings. List its key participants.**

**Model Answer:**

The **Delegation Event Model (DEM)** is a modern event-handling architecture introduced in Java 1.1 that decouples event generation from event processing using the **Observer Design Pattern**.

**Key Participants:**
1. **Event**: An object describing a state change (e.g., `ActionEvent`).
2. **Event Source**: The GUI component that generates events (e.g., `JButton`).
3. **Event Listener**: The object that receives and handles the event by implementing a listener interface (e.g., `ActionListener`).

**Workflow:** The source maintains a list of registered listeners. When an event occurs, the source iterates this list and invokes the appropriate interface method on each listener, delegating the responsibility of processing.

> [!NOTE]
> **Marks Distribution (KTU Pattern):** Definition: 1 mark | Three participants with examples: 1.5 marks | Workflow: 0.5 marks.

---

### Q2. **[KTU University Exam тАУ June 2024]**
**What is an Adapter class? Give two examples from `java.awt.event`.**

**Model Answer:**

An **Adapter Class** is a default (empty) implementation of a listener interface that contains **no abstract methods**. It is provided in `java.awt.event` to allow programmers to override only the methods they need, avoiding the boilerplate of writing empty bodies for unused interface methods.

**Examples:**
1. **`MouseAdapter`** тАФ implements `MouseListener` and `MouseMotionListener` with 7 empty methods. Used for handling only specific mouse events like click or hover.
2. **`WindowAdapter`** тАФ implements `WindowListener` with 7 empty methods. Commonly used to handle only `windowClosing` for graceful exit.

> [!NOTE]
> **Examiner Tip:** Always mention that adapter classes are used with **anonymous inner classes** for compact, modern Swing code.

