#### Model Solution to Q-A(b):

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class SimpleCalculator extends JFrame implements ActionListener {
    JTextField t1, t2, result;
    JButton addBtn, subBtn;

    public SimpleCalculator() {
        setTitle("Simple Calculator");
        setSize(300, 200);
        setLayout(new GridLayout(4, 2, 5, 5));
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        t1 = new JTextField();
        t2 = new JTextField();
        result = new JTextField();
        result.setEditable(false);
        addBtn = new JButton("Add");
        subBtn = new JButton("Subtract");

        addBtn.addActionListener(this);
        subBtn.addActionListener(this);

        add(new JLabel("Number 1:")); add(t1);
        add(new JLabel("Number 2:")); add(t2);
        add(addBtn); add(subBtn);
        add(new JLabel("Result:")); add(result);

        setVisible(true);
    }

    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        try {
            double n1 = Double.parseDouble(t1.getText());
            double n2 = Double.parseDouble(t2.getText());

            if (e.getSource() == addBtn) {
                result.setText(String.valueOf(n1 + n2));
            } else if (e.getSource() == subBtn) {
                result.setText(String.valueOf(n1 - n2));
            }
        } catch (NumberFormatException ex) {
            result.setText("Invalid Input");
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new SimpleCalculator();
    }
}
```

**Explanation of Key Event-Handling Logic:**

- The class implements `ActionListener` (Pattern 2).
- Both buttons are registered with `addActionListener(this)`.
- Inside `actionPerformed`, `e.getSource()` identifies **which button** triggered the event using reference equality.
- Input parsing uses `Double.parseDouble()` with `try-catch` to handle invalid input.
- The result is displayed in a non-editable `JTextField`.

> [!NOTE]
> **Marks Distribution:** GUI setup: 2 marks | Listener registration: 1 mark | `actionPerformed` logic: 2 marks | Exception handling: 1 mark | Output demonstration: 1 mark.

