#### Model Solution to Q-B(a):

**Difference Table:**

| Feature | `MouseListener` | `MouseMotionListener` |
|---|---|---|
| Events Handled | Click, press, release, enter, exit | Mouse moved, mouse dragged |
| Methods | 5 abstract methods | 2 abstract methods |
| Adapter | `MouseAdapter` | `MouseAdapter` (common) |
| Use Case | Discrete mouse interactions | Continuous tracking (drawing, drag) |

**Program:**

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class MouseDrawPanel extends JFrame {
    private JPanel canvas;
    private int prevX, prevY;
    private Graphics g;

    public MouseDrawPanel() {
        setTitle("Mouse Drag Demo");
        setSize(400, 400);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        canvas = new JPanel() {
            @Override
            public void paintComponent(Graphics g) {
                super.paintComponent(g);
                this.g = g;
            }
        };
        canvas.setBackground(Color.WHITE);

        canvas.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void mousePressed(MouseEvent e) {
                prevX = e.getX();
                prevY = e.getY();
            }
        });

        canvas.addMouseMotionListener(new MouseMotionAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void mouseDragged(MouseEvent e) {
                Graphics g = canvas.getGraphics();
                g.setColor(Color.RED);
                g.drawLine(prevX, prevY, e.getX(), e.getY());
                prevX = e.getX();
                prevY = e.getY();
            }
        });

        add(canvas);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new MouseDrawPanel();
    }
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Marks Distribution:** Difference table: 2 marks | Program structure: 2 marks | MouseListener logic: 1.5 marks | MouseMotionListener logic: 1.5 marks.

