## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mark-Loss Pitfalls in Event Handling Questions:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting `addXxxListener()` registration** тЖТ The event will fire but no handler runs. Always show the registration line explicitly.
> 2. **Confusing `getSource()` with `getActionCommand()`** тЖТ `getSource()` returns the **component object** (use `==` for comparison); `getActionCommand()` returns the **string label**. Mixing them is a common bug.
> 3. **Not using `WindowAdapter` for multi-method interfaces** тЖТ If a student implements `WindowListener` directly with 6 empty methods, the examiner deducts 1тАУ2 marks for not using the idiomatic adapter.
> 4. **Forgetting `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** тЖТ Program doesn't close on clicking the X. Lose 0.5 marks.
> 5. **Using `e.getKeyChar()` for arrow keys** тЖТ Returns a non-printable character. Use `e.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_UP` instead. This is a **favourite KTU trick question**.
> 6. **Not handling `NumberFormatException`** in calculator programs тЖТ Lose 1 mark for exception handling.
> 7. **Wrong method names** like `actionPerformed()` vs `ActionPerformed()` тЖТ Java is case-sensitive; auto-marking deducts.

